00:00:15.080 --> 00:00:16.320
8.

00:00:16.330 --> 00:00:20.360
Son Doong Cave
The Son Doong Cave in Vietnam is the world’s

00:00:20.360 --> 00:00:22.030
largest cave!!

00:00:22.030 --> 00:00:27.180
Translated as “Mountain River Cave” it
was first found by a man named Ho Khanh in

00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:28.180
1990.

00:00:28.180 --> 00:00:31.760
The farmer was trying to find shelter from
a storm when he notices water gushing out

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:33.030
of the limestone.

00:00:33.030 --> 00:00:37.059
He did the responsible thing and notified
the British Caving Research Association!

00:00:37.059 --> 00:00:40.120
Now you know what to do if you find something
amazing!

00:00:40.120 --> 00:00:42.879
Or you could keep it a secret of course, it
is up to you!

00:00:42.879 --> 00:00:47.590
BUT, he kind of got lost in the jungle and
forgot where it was for 18 years!!

00:00:47.590 --> 00:00:52.800
He stumbled upon it later and in 2010, the
BCRA went in to explore!

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:56.590
Son Doong Cave is so large, it has its own
ecosystem inside.

00:00:56.590 --> 00:01:00.480
It is over five kilometers long (3 miles)
and sometimes reaches heights of 200 meters

00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:04.080
(650 feet), that’s tall enough for rain
clouds to form!!

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:08.140
The river inside the cave after which it is
named after, is home to very unique species

00:01:08.140 --> 00:01:09.320
and organisms.

00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:14.020
The limestone cave is believed to have formed
some 2-5 million years ago when the underwater

00:01:14.020 --> 00:01:17.979
river found a fault and carved out the space
over time.

00:01:17.979 --> 00:01:23.350
Now thanks to the river, and sunlight that
comes through where the ceiling has collapsed,

00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:26.439
the place is full of wildlife.

00:01:26.439 --> 00:01:29.860
Explorers and tourists visiting the cave have
said spending the night there is actually

00:01:29.860 --> 00:01:31.310
quite noisy!!

00:01:31.310 --> 00:01:35.960
One of the most exciting things is the discovery
of previously unidentified species, such as

00:01:35.960 --> 00:01:39.970
many insects and birds, and even a new kind
of monkey!.

00:01:39.970 --> 00:01:44.080
There is much more of the cave to be explored
which is why many people call this mysterious

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:46.340
place, the lost world.

00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:47.340
7.

00:01:47.340 --> 00:01:51.040
Black Sea River
The Black Sea itself is located in Eurasia,

00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:53.790
between the Mediterranean and Caspian Sea.

00:01:53.790 --> 00:01:57.610
These waters were infamous for being inhospitable
and difficult to navigate.

00:01:57.610 --> 00:02:02.439
It’s shores were surrounded by savage tribes
and there were scary rumors of beasts in the

00:02:02.439 --> 00:02:03.439
water.

00:02:03.439 --> 00:02:08.369
However, one of the most intriguing secrets
of this sea is that there is actually a river

00:02:08.369 --> 00:02:10.980
underneath it that flows on the sea bed!

00:02:10.980 --> 00:02:14.880
This river was discovered by scientists from
the University of Leeds in 2010.

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:18.440
They used a robotic submarine to study a deep
channel.

00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:22.750
It has rapids stronger than the Thames and
if it were on land, it would be the world’s

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:24.500
6th largest river.

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:29.300
Maybe the coolest thing is that it even creates
waterfalls, underwater!!

00:02:29.300 --> 00:02:34.010
The notion of an underwater river wasn't foreign
to scientists, but the Black Sea River turned

00:02:34.010 --> 00:02:36.080
many theories their head.

00:02:36.080 --> 00:02:40.140
These underwater channels or rivers are hard
to explore because not only are they usually

00:02:40.140 --> 00:02:43.530
very deep, but powerful and unpredictable.

00:02:43.530 --> 00:02:47.730
The water that flows in this river is actually
much more salient than most of the water in

00:02:47.730 --> 00:02:48.870
the Black Sea.

00:02:48.870 --> 00:02:53.470
Since the water is denser and carries sediments
and nutrients into the ocean it is vitally

00:02:53.470 --> 00:02:56.470
important to life in the black sea.

00:02:56.470 --> 00:03:00.650
Upon further study, it was found that the
Black Sea River not only flows at about 4

00:03:00.650 --> 00:03:06.650
miles per hour with 22,000 cubic meters of
water passing through every second, it actually

00:03:06.650 --> 00:03:11.720
flows in the opposite direction of most rivers
on Earth when it comes to circling a bend.

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:14.470
Pretty cool to have a river under the sea!!

