00:08:22.669 --> 00:08:26.510
Owey Island Lake
The fun part about this place is that it is

00:08:26.510 --> 00:08:29.210
a lake, under a lake.

00:08:29.210 --> 00:08:33.979
Located in Donegal, Ireland, Owey Island is
a rocky islet with no permanent residents.

00:08:33.979 --> 00:08:38.820
On the northwest tip of the island there is
a lake on the cliff tops overlooking the ocean.

00:08:38.820 --> 00:08:41.940
So how did people find out there was a lake
underneath it?

00:08:41.940 --> 00:08:45.630
There is an extremely muddy sinkhole that
you can climb into that will take you to a

00:08:45.630 --> 00:08:48.120
silt beach in a cave.

00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:52.950
This lake is about 50 meters underground and
is fed by the Atlantic ocean and lake above

00:08:52.950 --> 00:08:54.200
that trickles below.

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:59.620
It is about 150 meters long and ends in a
pool known as the pool of tranquility.

00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:02.520
It is quite a magical place!

00:09:02.520 --> 00:09:06.630
As you descend into the cavern the walls are
covered with bioluminescent organisms that

00:09:06.630 --> 00:09:09.960
will help you find your way, then it is totally
dark.

00:09:09.960 --> 00:09:14.070
If you want to check out this place in person,
be sure to check out the company Unique Ascent

00:09:14.070 --> 00:09:16.380
because you don’t want to get lost down
there!

00:09:16.380 --> 00:09:18.320
And they have great tours!!

