00:09:19.510 --> 00:09:23.320
Mexican Cenotes
In the Yucatan peninsula there are nearly

00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:25.100
7,000 cenotes.

00:09:25.100 --> 00:09:30.450
Cenotes are underground caverns formed when
limestone caves in, revealing pools of water

00:09:30.450 --> 00:09:31.450
underneath.

00:09:31.450 --> 00:09:35.490
Their name comes from the Maya word for well
and most of them were found when people were

00:09:35.490 --> 00:09:40.120
wandering around, and then suddenly, the ground
would give way and you’d find yourself falling

00:09:40.120 --> 00:09:42.070
and splashing into a pool of water!

00:09:42.070 --> 00:09:47.190
They are created by naturally acidic water
filtering through and dissolving limestone.

00:09:47.190 --> 00:09:51.820
These mysterious underground pools were believed
by the Maya to be entrances to the underworld

00:09:51.820 --> 00:09:54.240
and have enormous sacred significance.

00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:59.550
In many there are still sacrificial remains
along with artifacts and stone altars and

00:09:59.550 --> 00:10:00.550
stairs.

00:10:00.550 --> 00:10:04.710
While most remain officially unexplored, you
can visit and even swim in them to experience

00:10:04.710 --> 00:10:07.710
the amazing mysterious places for yourself!

